The acoustic and thermodynamic variables used for the description of the behavior of the system are the density ρ, the temperature T, the pressure P, the particle velocity u, the mass entropy s, and the temperature of the solid TS. In the context of a linear description, these variables are written in the following form, the time dependence is usually chosen in eiωt:
